This	O
invention	O
relates	O
to	O
apparatus	O
for	O
forming	O
plastic	B-material
articles	O
,	O
and	O
,	O
more	O
particularly	O
,	O
relates	O
to	O
such	O
apparatus	O
for	O
forming	O
plastic	B-material
articles	O
by	O
a	O
thermoform	O
process	O
.	O
In	O
the	O
forming	O
of	O
plastic	B-material
objects	O
by	O
a	O
thermoform	O
process	O
,	O
it	O
is	O
conventional	O
to	O
provide	O
a	O
roll	O
of	O
plastic	B-material
stock	I-material
material	I-material
to	O
be	O
formed	O
into	O
the	O
desired	O
object	O
.	O
A	O
sheet	O
of	O
the	O
material	O
is	O
pulled	O
outwards	O
from	O
the	O
roll	O
and	O
disposed	O
over	O
a	O
die	O
or	O
mold	O
of	O
the	O
object	O
to	O
be	O
formed	O
and	O
then	O
sealed	O
along	O
the	O
periphery	O
of	O
the	O
mold	O
.	O
The	O
plastic	B-material
sheet	O
is	O
then	O
heated	O
to	O
a	O
point	O
where	O
it	O
becomes	O
pliable	O
.	O
Next	O
,	O
either	O
positive	O
pressure	O
is	O
applied	O
from	O
above	O
the	O
sheet	O
forcing	O
it	O
into	O
the	O
conforms	O
of	O
the	O
mold	O
or	O
,	O
in	O
the	O
alternative	O
,	O
a	O
vacuum	O
is	O
drawn	O
from	O
below	O
the	O
sheet	O
evacuating	O
the	O

Librarian	B-framework
Librarian	B-framework
is	O
a	O
framework	O
for	O
writing	O
bundlers	O

which	O
are	O
tools	O
that	O
resolve	O

,	O
and	O

a	O

.	O

your	O

An	O

)	O

existing	O

in	O

files	O
.	O

more	O

.	O

The	O
process	O

to	O

[	O
@	O
B1	O
]	O
-	O

@	O

]	O
)	O
.	O
This	O
process	O

.	O

are	O

together	O

their	O

particular	B-biological entity

.	O

by	O
individual	O

who	O

their	O

.	O

and	O

Disintegration	O
propensity	O
of	O
tablets	O
evaluated	O
by	O
means	O
of	O
disintegrating	O
force	O
kinetics	O
.	O
The	O
aim	O
of	O
this	O
work	O
was	O
to	O
measure	O
the	O
disintegrating	O
force	O
concomitantly	O

disintegration	O
propensity	O
of	O
tablets	O
.	O

and	O

were	O
measured	O
on	O

(	O

of	O
two	O

-	O

)	O

.	O

An	O
electrophotographic	O
printing	O
process	O
involves	O
creating	O
an	O
image	O
on	O
a	O
photoconductive	O
surface	O
or	O
photo	O
imaging	O
plate	O
(	O
PIP	O
)	O
.	O
The	O
image	O
that	O
is	O
formed	O
on	O
the	O
photoconductive	O
surface	O
is	O
a	O
latent	B-image
electrostatic	I-image
image	I-image
having	O
image	O
and	O
background	O
areas	O
with	O
different	O
electric	O
potentials	O
.	O
When	O
an	O
electrophotographic	O
ink	O
composition	O
containing	O
charged	B-particle
ink	I-particle
particles	I-particle
is	O
brought	O
into	O
contact	O
with	O
the	O
selectively	O
charged	O
photoconductive	O
surface	O
,	O
the	O
charged	B-particle
ink	I-particle
particles	I-particle
adhere	O
to	O
the	O
image	O
areas	O
of	O
the	O
latent	O
image	O
while	O
the	O
background	O
areas	O
remain	O
clean	O
.	O
The	O
image	O
is	O
then	O
transferred	O
to	O
a	O
print	O
substrate	O
(	O
e	O
.	O
g	O
.	O
paper	O
)	O
either	O
directly	O
or	O
by	O
first	O
being	O
transferred	O
to	O
an	O
intermediate	O
transfer	O
member	O
(	O
e	O
.	O
g	O
.	O
a	O
soft	O
swelling	O
blanket	O
)	O
and	O
then	O
to	O
the	O
print	O
substrate	O
.	O
One	O
component	O
of	O

Operating	O
System	O
(	O

)	O

to	O

software	O

.	O
When	O

system	O
fails	O
,	O

is	O
important	O
to	O
collect	O
the	O
memory	O
dump	O
for	O
diagnosis	B-process
or	O
problem	B-process
analysis	I-process
.	O
This	O
process	O
of	O
collecting	O
the	O
failed	O
system	O
memory	O

a	O
secondary	O
store	O

“	O

”	O
.	O
Typically	O

techniques	O

memory	O

to	O
a	O

secondary	O
storage	O
device	O
(	O

the	O
“	O
dump	B-hardware
device	I-hardware
”	O
)	O
before	O
the	O
system	O
reboots	O
.	O
Background	O

dumping	B-process

either	O

or	O
selected	O

of	O
the	O
system	O
memory	O
into	O
a	O
physical	B-hardware
device	I-hardware
.	O

a	O

application	O
and	O
typically	O
under	O
limited	B-resource

OS	O
.	O

method	I-process

.	O

.	O

Deep	O

.	O

*	O

*	O
.	O
